The Sheltered Housing Association against Ruthie Russo: “Saying 'This has a taste of protected housing' harms our activities."
Julie Gat, the head of the association, sent a letter in which she expressed the union's complaint against what they deemed a derogatory statement made by one of the judges of "The Next Restaurant" in one of the trailers for the program.
Ruthie Russo responded: "I'm glad that there are places that invest more in the culinary needs of this population."
The Association of Nursing Homes and Sheltered Housing in Israel against "the next restaurant": In a letter sent by Chairwoman Yuli Gat and received by "Israel Hayom" it is written as follows: "In advance of the broadcast, which was circulated on all social networks and television, it is described that the professional judge of the competition said 'there is a taste of sheltered housing in the food,' meaning food of a closed institution with low-quality food".
